  m_Name: Metatarsals_I_V_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Metatarsals_I_V_L
  partName: Metatarsals IV Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left fourth metatarsal forms part of the skeletal framework of the canine
    left hindpaw and extends between the tarsal region and the fourth digit. This
    bone supports weight-bearing activities while contributing to balanced paw mechanics
    and coordinated movement.
  - Muscles, tendons, and ligaments associated with the metatarsal enable controlled
    toe motion and stable hindpaw positioning during locomotion. It also plays an
    important role in shock absorption and efficient transfer of forces generated
    during movement.
